data.title: Daytona Sports Cars
data.text:
This article is about the Australian kit car maker. For the Borland Racing Developments car, see Daytona Sportscar.

Daytona Sports Cars Pty. Ltd. of Woodend, Victoria, Australia is a kit car maker that builds the X7 Road Rocket,[1] a car similar to the Lotus Super Seven but with a Holden LS1 engine. They currently manufacture a vehicle similar to the Shelby Daytona Coupe[2] in Dromana, Victoria.
